node.text:
I’m a firm believer in “it’s not how you start but how you finish” I might even agree with “It’s not where you start but where you are going” 
•
A mentor of mines told me years ago “The same thing you complaining about people has taken that and won with it!” that has stuck with me all these years!
•
No matter your current circumstances have a glass half full mentality. Look for the positives and be Greatful for what you do have and use that to start working towards a goal! 
•
Be resourceful, Find a mentor, work your ass off, and do more than enough! Go the extra mile. Push yourself and over time things will start to get better. You’ll start to get small wins. Use those small wins as momentum to keep building on and eventually you’ll see your harvest!
•
I hope this has inspired someone to keep going. And remember, the very things that you are complaining about people has taken that and won with it 🏆

node.text:
April is Financial literacy month 🔥 So I got up early this morning to share some Financial Tips on @fox40news with @msfesai 

I’ve been BOTH Poor and Rich, so I have a unique prospective when it comes to finances. I wasn’t taught about Financial literacy Growing up and it’s certainly not taught enough in school. Those are two of the many reasons why I am passionate about financial literacy 

I believe every Household in America should have a will & Trust! And Regardless of your income you should also have a Budgeting system to review your finances which can help you minimize debt 

And don’t overlook the value of having GOOD CREDIT 

Financial literacy should be taught in school and be just as important as any other subject! This will give kids a foundation and understanding of finances that many of us didn’t get

#financialliteracy 
#debtfree 
#budgeting 
#financialfreedom💰 
#education

node.text:
Last night I got to share my story on the biggest Stage in our profession in front of 50,000+ people from all around the world 🌎 

Let me show you How Good God is! Just six years ago I was staying with my parents. Who would have thought a kid from the inner cities of Miami would go on to build a massive multi million Dollar Business in any profession? I was a sanitation worker cleaning south beach just a few years ago! 

So how did I go from sanitation worker to where I am today ? 3 things. Write this down 

#1. BELIEF ( I BELIEVED without a shadow of a doubt that I would be successful!) 

#2. MENTORS (Find someone who has what you want and is willing to teach you HOW they got it) 

#3. OBSESSION (you going to have to be obsessed FOR A SEASON with whatever it is you trying to master. The Greats was Obsessed! Micheal Jordan was obsessed, Kobe Bryant was obsessed, Jeff bozos was obsessed! You MUST develop & master the SKILLS Necessary to win at a High level in whatever field you are in! 

Thank you again Eric & Marina for putting on such a powerful event and allowing me to share 

REMEMBER whatever you think about the most will grow & manifest 

Think about what you want in 2021. See it. Believe it. And do the work 💎🔨

node.text:
Trust me, you don’t want an easy life!
.
You want the strength and courage to endure and enjoy a hard life!
.
That strength only comes from self-imposed suffering and adversity.
.
Sadly, most people seek out comfort to an excess and become mentally and physically soft.
.
Don’t be one of these people, you’ll live to regret it!
.
In moment of extreme adversity you learn who you are and what you’re willing to pay to achieve your dreams of becoming your highest self.
.
In times of extreme adversity you will either negotiate the cost and miss out on who you’re meant to be...
.
...or you’ll pay your dues and become the version of yourself that you know lives within you!
.
We’re not born at our highest potential and purpose... we’re meant to develop into it.
.

node.text:
The opening Night of our convention had so many Fireworks 🧨 I had the Honor to Walk the stage to Receive My 5 million Dollar Earners Ring 💎  Huge Shotout to all my mentors Along the Journey and my incredible Team that’s filled with so many dynamic Leaders ! I appreciate all of you and certainly wouldn’t be here without you all 🏆

Who would’ve thought 5 years ago the kid from the inner cities of Miami that worked in the sanitation Department would go this Far 

Giving honor to God for all of these blessings 🙏🏾

And I hope I’m inspiring somebody out there. 

Remember, the journey of a million miles begins with ONE step! Take Action and Swing the bat and you to can hit a Homerun

node.text:
Happy Anniversary 🌟 to my Queen @morganhardman ❤️ Proverbs 18:22 22 “Whoever so findeth a wife findeth a good thing, and obtaineth favor of the Lord.”
•

Can’t believe it’s already been Four years of marriage! And boyyy have I received favor 🙏🏾 since you entered my life I’ve seen nothing but exceleration 🔋 My faith & Spiritual life has grown, My business 10X, my income hit numbers that most people won’t see in a lifetime. 

My love and appreciation for you goes beyond measure ❤️

Thank you for being an incredible mother to our children. A phenomenal wife. Outstanding business partner. And My Best friend ❤️ 

I love you Morgan Loraine Hardman ❤️❤️❤️ Here’s to next 100 Years 🥂

node.text:
I’m a firm believer in “it’s not how you start but how you finish” I might even agree with “It’s not where you start but where you are going” 
•
A mentor of mines told me years ago “The same thing you complaining about people has taken that and won with it!” that has stuck with me all these years!
•
No matter your current circumstances have a glass half full mentality. Look for the positives and be Greatful for what you do have and use that to start working towards a goal! 
•
Be resourceful, Find a mentor, work your ass off, and do more than enough! Go the extra mile. Push yourself and over time things will start to get better. You’ll start to get small wins. Use those small wins as momentum to keep building on and eventually you’ll see your harvest!
•
I hope this has inspired someone to keep going. And remember, the very things that you are complaining about people has taken that and won with it 🏆
